    <h1>About the MMBA</h1>

    <p>
      The <strong>Master Mariners Benevolent Association (MMBA)</strong> is one of San Francisco's oldest and most storied maritime organizations, originally founded in 1867. Its core mission has always been to foster participation in yachting and preserve the legacy of well-designed, properly constructed, and well-maintained classic and traditional wooden sailing craft.
    </p>
    <p>
      This website serves as a <strong>historical archive</strong> documenting the association's events, vessels, membership traditions, and the broader maritime community of San Francisco Bay.
    </p>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Archive Disclaimer</h3>
      <p>
        This website is maintained as a historical maritime archive and community resource. We are <strong>not affiliated</strong> with the Master Mariners Benevolent Association (MMBA), any successor organization, or any other entity currently operating under the Master Mariners name. Historical content belongs to its original authors and contributors.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>What This Site Documents</h2>
