      <li>A curated <a href="/links">maritime links directory</a> for Bay Area sailors</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The MMBA Legacy</h2>
    <p>
      Few yacht associations can trace their roots as far back as the MMBA. Founded by working boatmen — the schooner captains, hay scow skippers, and coastal traders of 19th-century San Francisco — the association grew into a beloved community of classic boat enthusiasts. For over a century, the annual regatta has brought together wooden yachts and traditional vessels in the same waters where San Francisco's maritime economy was built.
    </p>
    <p>
      The association publishes <a href="/shellback"><em>The Shellback</em></a>, a member newsletter that has documented club news, vessel restorations, and sailing adventures for decades.
    </p>

